  <cateringDescription><![CDATA[<p>The Terra Nova is on a half board basis.</p>
<p>Each morning a varied buffet breakfast is served from 7.30 - 9.30am. </p>
<p>When you return from a day on the slopes you can enjoy a three course meal. Starters and desserts are available from the buffet and the main course is served. </p>
<p>One raclette meal is included per week, just reserve at reception if you would like this.</p>
<p> </p>]]></cateringDescription>
  <deactivateThisPage>0</deactivateThisPage>
  <description><![CDATA[<p>If you are a keen skier then you'll be spoiled for choice staying here, with opportunities to discover the extensive <a data-udi="umb://document/37e8bc9846b74cf1a001f969874ce05b" href="/{localLink:umb://document/37e8bc9846b74cf1a001f969874ce05b}" title="Paradiski Ski Area">Paradiski Ski Area</a>. Each morning pop your skis on at the door for easy access to slopes, and when you return, you can enjoy a drink in the hotel bar and take in the views from the lounge area. Refuel at the panoramic restaurant with an extensive buffet breakfast and three course dinner. The position of Hotel le Terra Nova means that the bedrooms all have great views of the valley or the piste to make you appreciate that you really are in the mountains.</p>
<h2>Fantastic location </h2>
<p>Located in Plagne Centre and providing easy access to ski slopes and shops, Hotel le Terra nova offers you prime location that cannot be ignored. The hotel is positioned at the bottom of the slopes with convenient ski-in ski-out access and there is a chairlift departing next to the hotel - skis can come on and off right outside the hotel door! And an added bonus is that, due to it's high altitude of 2000 meters, you'll be sure to have excellent snow coverage for the duration of your stay.</p>
<h2>Family friendly</h2>
<p>Hotel le Terra Nova is a great choice for you and your family. Accommodation available ranges from family rooms large enough to sleep up to four or interconnecting rooms if you and the family would like your own spaces. The hotel caters well for young children, with the restaurant having high chairs and children's menus available, alongside the usual buffet offerings. Chillout in the hotel bar and lounge with lovely views across La Plagne or make the most of your quiet space and have some down time in the cosy bedrooms with access to flat screen TVs with a selection of channels. </p>]]></description>
